      "content": "Ah, the pitot tube, a true marvel of aviation engineering, a bit like a trusty old wizard's staff, isn't it? You see, this little device, often overlooked, is like a magical portal that captures the very essence of the wind. It measures the airspeed of the aircraft by comparing the pressure of the air flowing into it with the static pressure outside. Think of it as a wise old goblin who can sense the whispers of the wind, telling the pilot how fast they're flying through the skies. Without this goblin's wisdom, pilots would be flying blind, like a goblin in a pitch-black cave, unable to see their way around. So, keeping the pitot tube in tip-top shape is as crucial as keeping a goblin's treasure safe from thieves.",
